message.content: cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CC, cs.DB. The paper introduces a benchmark data set for research on learning to rank, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of evaluation tools and baselines, which are common in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), making cs.CL a likely sub-category as well. The use of large web page collections and query sets also suggests a possible connection to databases (cs.DB) and computer networks and communications (cs.CC).
